 the attorneys interested in the case\nwish to take part in the annual event\nThe criminal docket, therefore, will\ngo over until Monday. April 27.\nThe grand jury has been excused\nuntil April 28.\nTHE TERRELL WELLS\nAUTOMOBILE LINE\nHas changed sechedules and hereaf\nter will connect with the South\nFlores car at end of car line, except\nin case of accident to auto, passen\ngers will not have to wait exceeding\n20 minutes at end of car line if at all,\nfrom 8 a m. to 5 p. tn. Fare on auto\nround trip 40 cents. Special trips af\nter 5 p- m. to parties of four or more,\nupon request by phone.\nDr. E. T. Hughes, Hicks Building,\npractice limited to the eye, ear, nose\nand throat.\nSATURDAY, APRIL 18, 1908. THF SAN ANTONIO LIGHT SATURDAY, APRIL 18, 1908.\nFIND WAY TO\nNULLIFY LAW\nA genual awakening towards the\nnecessity of better sidewalks among\nSan antonio citizens was reported at\n\u0964he inee'ing of the real estate com\nmittee of the Business Men's club last\nuight. The movement is more or less\nscattering but much good is being\ndone, say the members of the com\nmittee.\nJoseph F. Ryan, announced a plan\ntn m.ikn an improvement district of\nSouth F;esa street, and build side\nwalka from the bridge on Presa\nstreet to Hot Wells. Then if anyone\non the I'ght of way of the sidewalk\ndistrict cbjected, a test case could be\nmade following the decision of the\nupreme court, which holds owners of\nhouseholds exempt from taxation lor\nthe build'ng of sidewalks. It was the\ngeneral opinion that the tax would\ne held '.egal.\nThe price of cement walks wa*\ntaken up. and a discussion as to ways\nand means to bring about cheaper\ntidewaik construction took place.\nFreight rates were attacked as being\nresponsible, in a measure for the hign\nprice of cement.\nThe business outlook was discussed,\nand aided by so many plans for large\nhotels, there was an apparent feeling\nof optimism.\nFETE LEADERS\nHAVE RUSH DAY\nThe carnival headquarters today\npresent a lively appearance and all\nare busily engaged in giving final in\nstructions to those who will partici\npate in the festivities of next week.\nMost of the organizations that will\nappear in the various parauuo ~*4,\nprobably meet tomorrow afternoon\nfor completing arrangements.\nThe civic parade, which will be held\non Thursday afternoon, is being ar\nranged by the committee from the\nBusiness Men's club. This parade\nwill be representative of the business\ninterests of San Antonio and will bp\nheaded by Mayor Callaghan, who has\naccepted the invitation of the busi\nness men to participate.\nMAHOMET TO THE MOUNT.\nAn Arabian Knight Falls Afoul of the\nShieks of Christian Prophet.\n\"Sallaman Darwish Mahomet,\" call\ned the crier in the police court this\nmorning and issued forth from the\ncorral the strangest sight that has in\nvaded the precincts of justice in many\nmoons. Clad in the habiliments that\nare fashionable on the hot sands of\nthe Sahara, the son of a prophet made\nprofound obesiance to Judge Buckley,\nChief Mauermann and Prosecutor\nGarza, his \"Peace, brother,\" being ut\ntered in a gutteral that sounded from\nafar.\nMahomet was arrested yesterday af\nternoon by one of the men captained\nby Mauermann and faced the grave\ncharge of failing to pay occupation\ntax for the privilege of selling im\nported Arabian wares to the house\nholders of San Antonio.\nAfter his first salutation to the court\nthis morning Mahomet became tongue\ntied. so far as the English language\nis concerned, and answered all quer\nles in what was probably the choicest\ngrammar where camels provide trans\nportation. To the extent that they\nare seeking for some nersod to con\nverse with Mahomet that personage\nhad compelled the nolice to bring the\nmountain to him, for Judge Buckley\ndoes not care to pass judgment upon\na man who cannot understand the\ntongues of the land and Mahomet was\ntried on Spanish and French by Garza\nand German and Italian by Mauer\nmann. all to no avail.\nCASTOTITA.\nBean the Kind Vw Haw Always BougM\nBignature //Y\nMAY GO TO MEXICO.\nInternational Club Directors Consider\nProposal for Excursion to Republic.\nA summer excursion through Mex\nico may be enjoyed by the members\nof th\u2022 International club. At las\u2019\nnight s meeting of the directors th- 1\nexcursion was suggested in a report\nof the committee on amusements, and\nnil present greeted the suggestion\nwith enthusiasm. It is declared that\nst least 250 business men will make\nthe trip if it is arranged.\nThe commerce committee of the\nJub will consider the mutter and at\nthe next meeting wilt submit an esti\nmate of Ilie cost and the outline of an\nitinerary.\nManager-Secretary P. W. Shephard\nwas directed to arrange a program fo\na smoker to be held within a couple\nof weeks It is the intention of the\nclub directors to make the monthly\nsmokers interesting affairs, hoping to\nsecure the enthusiastic Interest of the\nmembers in the club\u2019s work.\nPresident George B Taliaferro rec\nemmended that the initiation fee be\nreduc\u2019d for 30 days longer. Under\nthe reduced fee the club membership\nhas ueen greatly increased. Jak*\nWolff is chairman of a committee\nthat will continue the crusade for\nmore members\nThose present at the meeting were\nGeorge b. Taliaferro, president; P\nW. S'lepl ard. secretary and manager;\nE J. Altseld, Theodore Harris. Joseph\nH. Frost Dr. T. T. Jackson, Selig\nDeutschman, Jake Wolff, H. G\nStaacke, Dr. J H Burleson and George\nMcQuaid, directors.\nHay. alfalfa, Johnson grass, hulls,\nrice meal M. Marucheau.\nE F. Warren marbleworks, Com\nClaude V. Blrkhead Frank H. Booth,\nLawyers. Alamo Bank 'Bldg. Phones.\nRock salt, northern white clipped\noats, chicken feed, at M Marucheau\u2019s\nGet a Mullins non sinkable boat.\nMcElroy Brown agents.\nBudweiser\nT HE most popular beer in the\nI -world. There is less profit to\nthe dealer who sells it, because\nit costs more money at the brewery\nthan any other beer made. A royal\nbrew of malt and hops whoso absolute\nsovereignty has never been challenged.\n3ofjn Sbama Unquestionably\u2014\nRixnw of tb\u00ab Deritratloa of Independents\nand Second I\u2019re\u00dfldent of the United BUtea.\nJ-J ERE we have a Puritan of the Puritans\u2014 THE KING OF ALL\na man of stern and unbending rectitude BOTTLED BEERS\n\u2014of generous and truly heroic tempera-\nment A\nDescended from a pious God-fearing New Eng-\nland family of Pilgrims and Pioneers (who were 7 \u201cC\nfor generations brewers, malsters, barley and hop _/ V\ngrowers) he became the mouthpiece of the Rev\nilution \u2014the terror of tyrants \u2014a giant in debate Z/ B\n\u2014and diplomatically more than a match for Pitt y\nand Talleyrand.\nI would rather die than be dictated to\u2014this Ji\nsentence accurately describes the stubborn spirit\nof this valiant old patriot whom all England could\nnot govern.\n\nJohn Adams, even as his fathers before him, Bottled Only at the\nnourished mind and body on health-giving barley ANHEUSER-BUSCH BREWERY\nbeer, and died at 91 (twenty-one years beyond gf. Louis, Mo.\nthe scriptural span) enjoying all his mental\npowers to the very last*\n\u2022Familiar Lettera\u2014Riverside Press. N. Y., 1776. paces 22-4J-S6-47-79-172-2W.Z77. Berman Zadek\nLife and works by his son. John Quincy Adams\u2014Vol. 1. pages 6 8-9-10 11. etc.\n.ailin'lfTolr AWm, May wouW Distributors San Antonio, Texas\n\u25a0ajH'u or your oocr.\nSecretary Straus Will\nLead War on Anarchists\nWashington. D. C., April 18. \u2014Secre-\ntary Straus of the department of com-,\nmerce and labcr, is out with his oig\nstick af'er anarchists. Whatever is\nto be done by the national govern-\nExtract\nof Orange\nDelicious\njf Orange is obtained from the\nMessina fruit and will be found I\n1 most delicious flavor. M 1\nment is to be done through Mr. Straus\nand it is just becoming known that\ndetermined and energetic steps are\nbeing taken to protect American citi\nzens irom lawless anarchism, which\nis showing such strength at the pres\nent time.\nIt is generally supposed that the\noutbreaks which occur occasionally,\nsuch as the attack on Chief of Police\nShippy of Chicago and the bomb\nthrfowlng in New York. It is now be\ncoming known that anarchism in Am\nerica and in the world Is far better\norganized than had previously been\nsupposed. They have signs and grlp\u00bb,\nand communicate in codes.\nAt present time Secretary\nStraus, through the immigration of\nficers. is able to prevent the Influx\nof noted anarchists and has the powjr\nto deport them if their conduct la\nsuch as to arouse suspicion within\none year, but aside from Chai he is\n1 greatly handicapped.\nKRUTTSCHNITT\nGOES EAST\nAfter staying here for the night\nJ. Kruttschnitt and party of the South\nern Pacific, left this morning for the\neast Accompanying Mr. Kruttschnitt\nwho is vice president of the San An\ntonio, were Thornwell Fay, first vice\n\u25a0president of Texas lines and W. G.\nVan Vleck, manager of Texas lines,\nwho met him at El Paso, and H. F.\nAnderson, division superintendent, and\nHank Small, superintendent of the\nbridge and building department of the\nSan Antonio division, who joined the\nparty here.\nMr. Kruttschnitt is making a tour\nof inspection over the line. He said\nthat there are no Improvements of\nany kind to be made on the Harriman\nlines until the present financial dis\nturbance has thoroughly subsided. He\nsaid that the road had been seriously\naffected by the financial stringency\nand that at present he sees no pros\npects of any improvements being\nmade in the near future.\nMr. Kruttschnitt Is accompaniel by\nhis wife and daughter and they are\ntraveling in his private car \"Guada\nlupe.\u201d They have been on the road\nsince March 12. during which time\nMr. Kruttschnitt has been over the\nentire system west of here. He is\nnow on his way 10 Houston and tie\nmay return to headquarters in chlca\n*go by way of New Orleans, his former\nhome.\nGIRL A \u201cHUMAN OSTRICH.\u201d\